id: pm-fmjy
title: "CodeFactor/Duplication: remove duplicated code blocks (×20: 2 Critical, 3 Major, 15 Minor)"
description: "CodeFactor's duplicate-code detector found **20 clones**.\n\n## Breakdown + lists\n\n- Critical ×2 — https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Duplication&groupId=2\n- Major ×3 — https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Duplication&groupId=1\n- Minor ×15 — https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Duplication&groupId=4\n\n## Strategy\n\n- Production code: extract the duplicated block into a shared helper/constant/module. (This repo already favors shared dedup helpers — see prior chore pm-1b96.)\n- Test code: a large share of duplication lives in the command spec files (`create-command.spec.ts`, `update-command.spec.ts`); factor common arrange/act setup into shared test helpers or fixtures and parametrize repeated cases.\n- Tackle Critical + Major first.\n\n## Constraints\n\nBehavior-preserving. New shared helpers must themselves be covered to keep the 100% coverage gate green. Mind the 120-file/dir static cap if adding helper files."
type: Task
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[4]: code-quality,codefactor,duplication,refactor
